By Ejike Ejike, Abuja The inspector-general of police, IGP Mohammed Adamu, NPM, has ordered the immediate deployment of police intervention and stabilization forces to Oyo state to reclaim the public space, reinforce security and bolster public confidence in the areas affected by the recent crisis in the state. The deployments, consisting largely of intelligence and operational assets of the Force, include four units of the Police Mobile Force (PMF), seasoned operatives from the Force Intelligence Bureau and one operational/surveillance police helicopter from the police air-wing department. Force PRI, CP Frank MBA said the intervention force is charged with the responsibility of reinforcing and stabilizing security in the state, preventing further breakdown of law and order, protecting lives and properties and ultimately enhancing public safety and general security in the state.